.TH SXACL-VOLPERM "1" "September 2014" "sxacl @VERSION@" "Skylable SX Manual"
.SH NAME
sxacl-volperm \- manage volume permissions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sxacl volperm
\fR[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] \fI\,<username> sx://\/\fR[\fI\,profile@\/\fR]\fI\,cluster/volume\/\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBsxacl volperm\fR manages volume permissions for a specific user. It can be used to grant or revoke read/write access. Only volume owners and cluster administrators can change volume permissions.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-full\-help\fR
Print help, including hidden options, and exit
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-grant=<privilege>\fR
Grant a privilege on the volume to the user. The accepted values are "read", "write" or "read,write".
.TP
\fB\-\-revoke=<privilege>\fR
Revoke a privilege on the volume from the user. The accepted values are "read", "write" or "read,write".
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config\-dir\fR=\fI\,PATH\/\fR
Path to the SX configuration directory (default: ~/.sx)
.TP
\fB\-D\fR, \fB\-\-debug\fR
Enable debug messages.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
To grant user 'joe' full access to the volume 'data' run:
.br
\fB    sxacl volperm \-\-grant=read,write joe sx://admin@cluster/data\fP
.br

To make sure user 'joe' has only read-access to the volume 'data' run:
.br
\fB    sxacl volperm \-\-grant=read \-\-revoke=write joe sx://admin@cluster/data\fP
.br
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBsxacl-volshow\fR(1)
